doc.previous: Saskatchewan is par excellence the wheat growing region of Canada Its plains are famous for their fertility They extend from the international boundary practically to Prince Albert 53 deg 15 min N lat where the northern forest which itself contains important stretches of agricultural land commences Adapted from Catholic Encyclopedia 1913 Saskatchewan and Alberta
